	Events take place on the 3rd Sunday of each month. Please note the followi
	ng upcoming dates: \n\nFebruary 15th\n\nMarch 15th\n\nApril 19th\n\nMay 17
	th\n\nJune 21st\n\nJuly 19th \\(37th Annual Indian Days Powwow Weekend\, s
	tarting at 9:00 AM\\)\n\nTiming and Location Details \n\nStart Time: 10:00
	 AM\n\nLocation: Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center \\(5011 Bernie White
	bear Way Seattle\, WA 98199\\)\n\nMeeting Point: Meet at the Powwow Ground
	s\n\nThis event is FREE for all! \n\nLace up your shoes and enjoy the scen
	ic trails while connecting with the community! For more information about 
	the venue and organizing group\, please email communications@unitedindians
	.org\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/daybreak-star-commun
